UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 37/EN
1 substantial demands on local communities and their fiscal resources; and
2 WHEREAS, increasing public awareness of animals in shelters or in the care of
3 rescue organizations can lead to higher adoption rates for those purebred and mixed-
4 breed animals; and
5 WHEREAS, many dogs, including breeds with deep Kentucky roots, purebreds,
6 and mixed breeds alike, become loyal companions in homes across the Commonwealth
7 of Kentucky; and
8 WHEREAS, it is fitting that as Kentucky designates an official state dog, that the
9 General Assembly also recognizes the importance of promoting the adoption and
10 responsible care of purebred and mixed-breed animals in shelters and in rescue
11 organizations; and
12 WHEREAS, the eastern spotted skunk and eastern hellbender are native, nongame
13 species historically present within Kentucky; and
14 WHEREAS, the eastern hellbender is classified as a species of greatest
15 conservation concern, and the eastern spotted skunk is classified as a species of high
16 conservation concern; and
17 WHEREAS, official recognition of these species promotes environmental
18 education, conservation awareness, and appreciation of Kentucky's natural heritage
19 without fiscal or regulatory impact;
20 NOW, THEREFORE,
21 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
22 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 2 IS CREATED TO
23 READ AS FOLLOWS:
24 The Treeing Walker Coonhound is named and designated as the official state dog of
25 Kentucky.
26 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 2 IS CREATED TO
27 READ AS FOLLOWS:
Page 2 of 3
SB003720.100 - 1058 - XXXX 4/15/2026 10:54 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 37/EN
1 Domestic cats (Felis catus) and dogs (Canis familiaris), both purebred and mixed
2 breeds alike, that reside in or have been adopted from Kentucky animal shelters or
3 rescue organizations are named and designated as the official pets of the
4 Commonwealth of Kentucky.
5 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 2 IS CREATED TO
6 READ AS FOLLOWS:
7 The eastern spotted skunk (Spilogale putorius) is named and designated as the official
8 state nongame mammal of Kentucky.
9 SECTION 4. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 2 IS CREATED TO
10 READ AS FOLLOWS:
11 The eastern hellbender (Cryptobranchus alleganiensis) is named and designated as the
12 official state amphibian of Kentucky.
